The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on the text-to-SQL problem, which involves generating SQL queries from natural language questions. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves working with tables and leveraging their content, which suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB). The use of deep learning models such as BERT also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques such as encoding feature vectors, which suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
